      <persName role="Press Photographer"><forename>Namık</forename><surname>Görgüç</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.7d5d8ec5">Görgüç, Namık</ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A man in a dark coat and a felt cap is standing in front of the display of an Aşure stand. He is holding a spoon in his right hand and eating something with his left. The market stand is in front of him with displays of Aşure and a large metal kettle. A man in a felt cap and apron is busy with the kettle and at the same time looks towards the customer and the camera. In the background, a wall belonging to <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=Y1">Yeni cami</ref>.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">Aşure is a dessert made of beans, chickpeas, wheat, rice, raisins, walnuts, pomegranate and sugar. It is widespread in Turkey and the Middle East.</ab>
